            <subject>Re: Q&amp;A for lecture 2</subject>
            <message>&lt;p&gt;The easiest way to understand this is to consider a system that has only a delay associated with it.  In other words, what is sent in will come out $$D$$ time units after.  Thus, we have $$y(t) = u(t-D)$$, where, $$y$$ and $$u$$ are output and input, respectively.&lt;/p&gt;</message>
