            <subject>Re: Q&amp;A for lecture 2</subject>
            <message>&lt;p&gt;It is difficult to imagine a noncausal system.  But this is possible when space is the independent variable, as opposed to time being independent.  In this case, future value will actually refer to a value that is ahead in position.  This idea is useful to explain some concepts also.  For example, in Shannon's reconstruction theorem (which we will see in the near future), we will see that the formula is noncausal.&lt;/p&gt;</message>
